The paper proposes new deep learning strategies for image segmentation, specifically for brain tissue segmentation on infant brain MRI. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also focuses on improving the performance of DenseNets, which is a popular deep learning architecture used for image segmentation, and proposes new training strategies using similarity loss functions and patch prediction fusion. This suggests that the paper may also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions achieving top performance in a segmentation challenge, which suggests that it may also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
